        "subject": "LU-930 gnilnd: fix whitespace and style issues",
        "message": "LU-930 gnilnd: fix whitespace and style issues\n\nFix basic code style issues with the gnilnd code:\n- explicit values in UAPI enums to avoid bugs if added/removed\n- fix comment style to avoid triggering space-intent checks\n- use tabs instead of spaces for declaration alignment\n- wrap comment lines at 80 columns in nearby code\n\nThere are still many more style issues in the function declaration\nblocks (lines over 80 chars, spaces for alignment), and many other\ncheckpatch warnings, but too many to fix in this patch.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I13e431d535ef868941e8bbd0a8008acf0b3ebbe5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63415\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Caleb Carlson <caleb.carlson@hpe.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
